<body>
    <h1>Deposits On Hand</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrappe=
r confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image =
image-center" width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"ac3da55d45198c4e93ace73=
6b2a30adf96b4f5b121c34fb7a593d148ac1a809a" data-image-src=3D"https://minist=
rybrands.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/7369818146/image-20260706-=
221334.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1783376015927&amp;cacheVersio=
n=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"421" data-width=3D"1807" data-unresolved=
-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"7370571855" data-linked-res=
ource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-re=
source-default-alias=3D"image-20260706-221334.png" data-base-url=3D"https:/=
/ministrybrands.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"im=
age/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"7369818146" data-linked-resou=
rce-container-version=3D"16" data-media-id=3D"5d90f7a3-ca74-46fd-81ef-e5783=
19962f2" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"109"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p><strong>How to read this page.</strong> Everything here is specific to D=
eposits On Hand and its dashboard widget. Sections 1 to 3 are what exists t=
oday, validated in a live audit on asmdev (13 Jul 2026). Section 5 is the d=
esigner brief: jobs, scenarios, states, and constraints in one place. Statu=
s marks: <span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh=
 aui-lozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> checked in the product, <span cl=
ass=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-lozenge-comp=
lete">DESKTOP RESEARCH</span> sourced from public material, <span class=3D"=
status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-lozenge-current">TO=
 CONFIRM</span> open. General dashboard design principles live in a separat=
e reference document, not on this page. Sources at the bottom.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-1.WhatDepositsOnHandis">1. What Deposits On Hand i=
s</h2>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> Deposits On Hand is the module behind =
the widget. A deposit account is money the organization holds on behalf of =
a <strong>depositor</strong> (a person or organization from Records). The s=
tructure is a three-level hierarchy:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Level</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>What it is</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example from asmdev</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Group</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Top-level grouping of account types</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>NW Group</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Account Type</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Category with its own interest settings; populates the widget filter</p>=
</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>NW Group/Jo's Account Type 1</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Account</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>One depositor's account: name, number, inception date, balance, active s=
tatus</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Nicole whatnot, #123456</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> An account's lifecycle: created and ed=
ited in Modify &gt; Account Information; money moves via Enter &gt; Transac=
tion (deposit, withdrawal, adjustment); withdrawals generate a check in Acc=
ounts Payable; interest is calculated and posted in batch by Utilities &gt;=
 Post Interest Deposits; closing happens through a Close Account dialog tha=
t posts final interest through a chosen date; depositor statements are conf=
igured in Modify &gt; Statement Design.</p>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-complete">DESKTOP RESEARCH</span> Who runs this in the real world: d=
enominational headquarters and church extension funds, where congregations =
and individuals deposit money that the body pays interest on and lends to a=
ffiliated churches. These are regulated securities programs, not FDIC-insur=
ed bank accounts. This makes the widget a small portfolio view over deposit=
or money, a different thing from the Bank Balances widget (operational cash=
).</p>
<p><strong>The role of account type.</strong> <span class=3D"status-macro a=
ui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-lozenge-complete">DESKTOP RESEARC=
H</span> Type is the product line of a deposit program: interest settings l=
ive at type level, Post Interest runs off type-driven accrual settings, and=
 real extension funds structure offerings this way (demand investments, fix=
ed-rate term certificates, IRA-type accounts at LCEF and Disciples CEF). Fo=
r the HQ administrator, <strong>type is the portfolio dimension</strong> (h=
ow much sits in each product, where interest liability concentrates) and <s=
trong>account is the depositor dimension</strong> (who called, what is thei=
r balance).</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Naming:</strong> the widget says "Deposit Accounts", the module =
says "Deposits On Hand". Same thing, two names, on the same screen. <span c=
lass=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-lozenge-suc=
cess">VERIFIED LIVE</span> Decision on the table: rename the widget to matc=
h the module (Section 8, Gap 9).</p>
</blockquote>
<h2 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-2.Thewidgettoday">2. The widget today</h2>
<p>Original documentation from the first version of this page, validated in=
 the live audit. Data source: active accounts from the Deposits On Hand mod=
ule (tables DHAccount for accounts, DHTypeRepository for the type filter), =
balances calculated as of today, ordered by name then inception date.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Behavior</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Status</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Left: table of active accounts with Name, Inception Date, Account#, Endi=
ng Balance, and a totals row (# accounts, combined balance). The table is a=
 <strong>flat list of individual accounts at every volume</strong>: with Sh=
ow All it mixes accounts across every type, and with a type selected it lis=
ts that type's accounts. There is no Type column. Account types never appea=
r as table rows; type totals exist only as pie segments read by hover</p></=
td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span>, flat account-level listing confirmed =
by product owner (13 Jul 2026)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Right: pie chart "By Account Type", one segment per type, value shown on=
ly on hover</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Account type dropdown filters the table only; the pie always shows all t=
ypes. Reproduced: filter to an empty type and the table says "No records to=
 display" while the pie still shows the other type</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Refresh is a link labeled "Last refreshed &lt;date time&gt;": the timest=
amp is the button. It does not update when the filter re-renders the data, =
only on explicit refresh</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>No drill-down: rows and pie segments are not clickable. The widget title=
 is a link, but it opens the widget chooser (17 panel options), not the mod=
ule</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-3.Themoduletoday:noreadlayer">3. The module today:=
 no read layer</h2>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> Walked the full module to test where a=
 widget drill-down could land. Finding: <strong>there is nowhere to land.</=
strong> Unlike Accounts Payable (View &gt; Transaction Inquiry), Deposits O=
n Hand has no View menu, no live activity table, no interest history, no li=
st of closed accounts. Everything is entry, edit, action, or report:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Menu</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Pages</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Nature</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Enter</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Transaction</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Data entry per depositor</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Manage</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Unposted Transactions</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Queue of entries awaiting posting, not history</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Reports</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Links out of Financials to a separate reporting application</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Criteria form, then a document. The only place Interest, Unposted Intere=
st, and movement columns exist</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Modify</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Group Information, Account Type Information, Account Information, Statem=
ent Design</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Setup and edit. Account Information is a search (group, type, depositor,=
 name, number, active/inactive) that opens one account at a time; closing l=
ives here</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Utilities</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Post Interest Deposits, Inactivate or Renew an Account, Change Interest =
Rates</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Batch action wizards, no status view of what is due</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><strong>In practice:</strong> "which accounts have unposted interest" =
=3D run a Columnar or Detail report in the separate reports app. "Which acc=
ounts closed recently" =3D search Account Information with Show Only Inacti=
ve, one account at a time. "Did the payout go through" =3D leave the module=
 and find the check in Accounts Payable.</p>
<h2 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-4.Personas">4. Personas</h2>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-complete">DESKTOP RESEARCH</span> Deposits On Hand is a headquarters=
 feature, which inverts our usual persona hierarchy: the part-time church a=
dmin is secondary here.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Persona</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Relationship to this widget</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>P1. HQ finance administrator (primary)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Staff accountant at a denominational HQ, district office, or extension f=
und. Manages depositor accounts, posts interest, processes withdrawals via =
AP, answers depositor questions, reports to leadership and regulators.</p><=
/td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>P2. Part-time church admin or bookkeeper (secondary)</strong></p=
></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Often part time (a real posting: 20 hrs/week at $20/hr) or volunteer, no=
 formal accounting training. Touches this widget only if the org runs depos=
it accounts, or misreads it as bank balances.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>P3. Treasurer / finance committee (oversight)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>High-capacity volunteer doing review, not data entry. Needs totals and t=
rend for board reporting and anomaly spotting.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>P4. Depositor-facing service staff (contextual)</strong></p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>At extension funds, staff field depositor calls about balances, rates, m=
aturities. The account grid is their fastest lookup.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-5.Designerbrief">5. Designer brief</h2>
<div class=3D"panel" style=3D"background-color: #EAE6FF;border-color: #998D=
D9;border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"panelContent" style=3D"background-color: #EAE6FF;">
<p>Everything a designer needs to start: the jobs, the scenarios they play =
out in, every widget state, and the constraints that bound the solution. Re=
ad with Section 7 (design direction) and Section 8 (gaps).</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-5.1Jobstobedone">5.1 Jobs to be done</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Job</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>When / so that</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Possible today?</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>1. Portfolio pulse check</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Opening Financials, see total on deposit and mix by type, confirm nothin=
g unexpected</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-current">PARTLY</span> Total and count yes; type mix only via hover =
on the pie, no type totals in text</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>2. Single account lookup</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Depositor calls, find their account and balance in seconds</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-current">PARTLY</span> Widget grid works only at small volumes (no s=
earch); otherwise Account Information search, one account at a time</p></td=
>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>3. Interest cycle assurance</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Posting date approaches, see which accounts have accrued or unposted int=
erest, run Post Interest on time</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-error">NO</span> Only via reports in the separate reports app</p></t=
d>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>4. Liquidity oversight</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Leadership asks about position, show balance in context (trend, movement=
)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-error">NO</span> No trend, delta, or history anywhere except reports=
</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>5. Anomaly detection</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A balance moved unexpectedly, surface the change before month end</p></t=
d>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-error">NO</span> Static balances only</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>6. Drill to action</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Widget shows something needing work, click through and handle it</p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-error">NO</span> No drill-down, and no destination exists (Section 3=
)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><strong>Non-jobs:</strong> transaction entry, bank reconciliation (Bank =
Account Management), donation batch posting (giving side).</p>
<h3 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-5.2Contextscenarios">5.2 Context scenarios</h3>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-complete">DESKTOP RESEARCH</span>, grounded in the verified module m=
ap. Each ends with how it plays out today.</p>
<p><strong>A. Monday morning at a district office.</strong> The HQ administ=
rator opens the dashboard, sees the total and type mix. One type looks lowe=
r than last week. Today: no comparison exists, so "lower" depends on memory=
; investigating means a report in the separate reports app.</p>
<p><strong>B. Depositor phone call.</strong> A congregation treasurer asks =
their balance and when interest last posted. Today: staff can scan the grid=
 for the balance if the list is short; the interest question requires a Det=
ail report. No search, no click-through.</p>
<p><strong>C. Quarter-end interest run.</strong> The administrator wants to=
 know which accounts accrue this quarter and whether anything is unposted b=
efore running Post Interest. Today: nothing signals this; the Columnar repo=
rt is the only pre-check.</p>
<p><strong>D. Board packet week.</strong> The treasurer needs deposits by t=
ype, trend vs last quarter, and totals readable by non-accountants. Today: =
type totals exist only in the pie (hover to read); trend does not exist; th=
e packet gets built from reports.</p>
<p><strong>E. Small church edge case.</strong> A part-time admin at a churc=
h that does not use Deposits On Hand selects the widget expecting bank bala=
nces and gets an empty grid. Today: "No records to display" with blank tota=
ls, no explanation, no way forward.</p>
<h3 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-5.3Widgetstates">5.3 Widget states</h3>
<p>Every state the widget can be in, with its rule. States 1 to 4 and the t=
ooltip are agreed spec; loading and error are proposed defaults.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>State</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Rule</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Status</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>1. Org does not have the module</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The widget does not appear in the widget chooser and cannot be selected.=
 No teaser, no locked state.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-current">TO CONFIRM</span> how module entitlement is detected (licen=
se flag vs security rights); today the chooser appears to list all 17 panel=
s regardless</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>2. Module present, user has no rights</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The widget is hidden for that user, consistent with the Bank Balances pr=
ecedent of per-user rights.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-current">TO CONFIRM</span> whether widget visibility respects module=
 rights today</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>3. Module present, zero accounts</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Purposeful empty state: names the module, one line on what the widget sh=
ows, and a <strong>+ Add Account</strong> action opening Deposits On Hand (=
Modify &gt; Account Information, new account). Action visible only to users=
 with rights to create accounts; everyone else gets the explanation without=
 the button.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">SPEC AGREED</span> (13 Jul 2026)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>4. Accounts exist, filter matches none</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Explicit zeros (# Accounts: 0, balance 0.00 in the org's currency), caus=
e stated ("No accounts of this type"), <strong>Show all</strong> action cle=
ars the filter. No chart for zero data; a short text line takes its place.<=
/p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">SPEC AGREED</span> (13 Jul 2026)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>5. Loading</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Skeleton in the widget's final layout, no layout shift, no spinners over=
 stale numbers.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-current">PROPOSED</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>6. Data error</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If balances cannot be loaded, show a clear message and a Retry action. N=
ever render stale figures without their "data as of" stamp; a wrong balance=
 is worse than no balance for regulated figures.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-current">PROPOSED</span></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><strong>Info tooltip copy.</strong> <span class=3D"status-macro aui-loze=
nge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-lozenge-success">SPEC AGREED</span> (13 =
Jul 2026) Shown from the widget's info icon on hover and on keyboard focus,=
 dismissible (WCAG 1.4.13). The same copy serves as the widget's descriptio=
n in the widget chooser:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Balances of the deposit accounts your organization holds for depositors,=
 such as congregations or individuals whose funds you manage and pay intere=
st on.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-5.4Constraints">5.4 Constraints</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Constraint</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>What it means for the design</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Rights and PII</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Accounts carry depositor names and balances. Per-account visibility foll=
ows user rights (Bank Balances precedent). No account data in states visibl=
e to unauthorized users.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Segregation of duties</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Custody, recording, and review are separate roles in church finance. The=
 widget stays read-and-navigate; create and edit actions appear only behind=
 rights (see state 3).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Regulatory accuracy</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Balances feed depositor statements and extension-fund investor reporting=
 (NASAA-regulated). Every figure needs a visible "data as of" stamp and mus=
t reconcile to the module.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Account identity</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Two accounts can share the same <strong>name</strong> and be different a=
ccounts, distinguished only by account number (verified with the product ow=
ner). Any list, drill, or comparison must keep same-named accounts unambigu=
ous (see Gap 14).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Org-driven formatting</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Currency and dates come from the organization's locale, never the client=
's or server's. The live audit rendered =C2=A3 and dd/mm/yyyy on a US produ=
ct (Gap 12).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Plain language</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Volunteers and part-timers run this market. Labels like "Total on deposi=
t" and "Interest not yet posted", never module jargon.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Accessibility</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>WCAG 2.1 AA per the Pathway Accessibility Gate. All values available as =
text (no hover-only data), one semantic table with header association, labe=
led controls, keyboard-reachable tooltip.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Framework reality</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The dashboard is ASP.NET Web Forms: two widget slots, full postbacks, pa=
nels swapped via the title link. Interactive patterns cost more here; a ful=
l-width view may be framework work.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Reports live in a separate application</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Any "open report" link leaves Financials. Label such links honestly ("Op=
ens in Reports") and treat the transition as a designed moment.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Legacy continuity</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Long-tenured users report navigation confusion after past changes. Renam=
es and layout changes need continuity cues (subtitle, tooltip, unchanged da=
ta meaning).</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-6.Competitorandanalogbenchmark">6. Competitor and =
analog benchmark</h2>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-complete">DESKTOP RESEARCH</span> No competitor has a "deposits on h=
and" widget by that name; the closest analogs are account-balance widgets. =
The bar they set: <strong>balance + status + one-click action into a live s=
creen.</strong> Their drill-downs work because a live screen already sits b=
ehind the card; Section 3 shows we lack that screen. Scale also differs: Xe=
ro and QBO list 3 to 10 bank accounts per org, while a deposit program hold=
s hundreds to thousands of depositor accounts (Disciples CEF alone: 2,000+ =
individual and 800+ congregation investors), which is why the account grain=
 does not fit our dashboard the way it fits theirs.</p>
<div id=3D"expander-760721780" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-760721780" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"9b45ae8c85c16a66aad904c0270f58d8cbd79c=
476bc8d003bcec7b51f05e1f85" width=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=
=3D"expand-control-text">Benchmark detail (7 products)</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-760721780" class=3D"expand-content">
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"960" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluence=
Table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Product</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Pattern</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Xero</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>One widget per bank account: balance, count of unreconciled lines, last =
import date; the count deep-links into the reconcile flow. Plus an Account =
Watchlist for any GL account (this month + YTD).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>QuickBooks Online</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Bank Accounts card plus Cash Flow tab; dashboard flags items needing att=
ention; widgets addable/removable.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Aplos</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Cash position as the headline value; instant clarity over dense grids.</=
p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Sage Intacct (nonprofit)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Role-based dashboards; Cash Analysis shows months of operating reserves =
in real time.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>AccuFund (nonprofit)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Computes days cash on hand, current ratio, LUNA on the dashboard; market=
s it as a differentiator.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Realm / ACS</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Flow integration (giving batches post as deposits); no deposit-account w=
idget.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Grain Ledger</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Exception-first: mismatches surfaced explicitly, reports readable by non=
-accountants.</p></td>
