</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-7.Designdirection:threedepthlevels">7. Design dire=
ction: three depth levels</h2>
<p><strong>Grain decision.</strong> The widget's dashboard grain is the <st=
rong>account type</strong> (one row per type: name, # accounts, total balan=
ce, share), not the individual account. An org has a handful of types but h=
undreds to thousands of accounts, so only the type grain fits a glance; typ=
e is where interest settings and portfolio thinking live (Section 1); and a=
 text type-summary replaces both the flat account list and the hover-only p=
ie, resolving Gaps 1 and 5 in one component. Individual accounts move to L3=
 behind a click, with a Type column and search. Note the account grid must =
keep accounts distinguishable when two share a name: the current widget rel=
ies on its Account# column for this, so the L3 grid must retain the account=
 number (see Gap 14).</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Level</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Size</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Content</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Question answered</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Scope</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>L1. KPI tile</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Single card</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Total on deposit, # accounts, delta vs prior period, one status badge (i=
nterest run due / unposted interest)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Is everything okay, what is the total?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Widget</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>L2. Standard widget</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Half width</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>L1 + <strong>type summary</strong>: one row per account type with # acco=
unts, total balance, share (labeled bar), each row clickable. Replaces the =
flat account list and the pie</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>What is the mix, what changed?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Widget</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>L3. Inquiry surface</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Full width</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Account-level grid, searchable, with <strong>Type column</strong>, accou=
nt number, balance, last activity, interest status, active/inactive; 12-mon=
th trend, movement, export, links to reports and Post Interest. Opens filte=
red to a type when reached from an L2 row</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Which account, what happened, what next?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Module + data layer.</strong> This is the read layer the module =
never had (Section 3), not a bigger widget</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-7.1Timerangeandchartaxes">7.1 Time range and chart=
 axes</h3>
<p>Deposits On Hand shows a <strong>balance</strong>, not a flow. A balance=
 has a meaningful value on any given day (money sitting on deposit right no=
w), unlike Payroll Distributions where the headline is a sum of what moved =
over a span. That one difference decides how time works here and what the a=
xes are, and it makes this widget behave in the opposite way to the Payroll=
 one.</p>
<p><strong>The Y axis is always the balance amount</strong> (total on depos=
it, in the organization's currency). It does not change with the time range=
 or the view. Whatever span or granularity is chosen, the vertical axis is =
money on deposit.</p>
<p><strong>The X axis, and what "time range" means, depends on which of two=
 views the widget is in.</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>View</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>What the time range does</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>X axis</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Y axis</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Snapshot (composition)</strong>, the L1 total and L2 by-type mix=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Sets the <strong>as-of date</strong> (default today). A single point in =
time, no trend</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Account type (the bars or segments of the mix)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Balance as of that date</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Trend (over time)</strong>, the L3 balance history</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Sets the <strong>window</strong> shown</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Time, plotted as end-of-period points</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Balance as of each period end (not a sum of activity in the period)</p><=
/td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>Because a balance only steps when money moves (deposits, withdrawals, an=
d above all the batch interest posting), the natural X granularity for the =
trend is the <strong>fiscal period</strong> (or month), not days. A daily b=
alance line for a deposit fund would be mostly flat with occasional steps; =
period-end points carry the signal without the noise.</p>
<p><strong>Proposed time spans (recommendation, to confirm).</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Span</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Use</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Default granularity</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>As of today</strong> (snapshot, default)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The everyday pulse check: today's total and mix. Always the default</p><=
/td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Single point</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Trailing 12 months</strong> (trend)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The core liquidity-oversight view (JTBD 4): rolling, always meaningful r=
egardless of fiscal boundaries. This is the "12-month trend" already named =
at L3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Month or period end, about 12 points</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>This fiscal year to date</strong> (trend)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Running position within the current reporting year; aligns to board and =
annual reporting</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Fiscal period</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Last fiscal year</strong> (trend or snapshot)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The closed year for year-end reporting and comparison; a period-end line=
, or an as-of-year-end figure for a board packet</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Fiscal period</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Custom range</strong> (trend)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Always available (a hard requirement carried from the Payroll work). Cov=
ers any reporting window a user needs</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Steps from period to quarter as the range lengthens</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><strong>Quarter (this or last)</strong> is a reasonable secondary span f=
or the board cadence, but a quarter holds only about three period points, a=
 thin trend, so I would treat it as optional rather than core.</p>
<p><strong>On fiscal period specifically.</strong> For a balance widget, fi=
scal period never goes on the Y axis; Y is always the balance. Fiscal perio=
d belongs on the <strong>X axis</strong> as the tick interval for the trend=
 (one point per period end) and as the anchor for an as-of snapshot ("balan=
ce as of end of Period 6"). It fits this widget well because it is already =
first-class product context (the top-right switcher runs on fiscal year and=
 period) and because interest posts on that cadence, so period ends are exa=
ctly where balances step. So fiscal-aligned spans belong in the list, and f=
iscal period is the natural granularity, not a quantity on the Y axis.</p>
<p><strong>Compare-to options for MVP.</strong> Under the trend, the "compa=
re to" selector (the baseline the current balance is measured against to pr=
oduce the change figure, delta, or trend line) ships for MVP with these ite=
ms: <strong>previous week, previous month, previous quarter, previous fisca=
l year, and previous calendar year</strong>. These are deliberately simple =
and standard. This is new functionality, the data layer is still unclear, a=
nd there is not yet enough research to justify anything more elaborate, so =
MVP keeps the baseline set small and conventional; feedback over time will =
guide what to adjust or add to make it more usable in future.</p>
<p><strong>The gate (same shape as the pay-group question on the Payroll wi=
dget).</strong> Every trend span assumes we can obtain historical period-en=
d balances. The live audit (Section 3) found the module has no history surf=
ace: balances are computed as of today, and movement and interest history l=
ive only in the separate reports application. So a balance-over-time trend =
depends on the data layer being able to reconstruct period-end balances fro=
m the deposit transaction history (DHAccount), or it is a data-layer build.=
 The snapshot spans (as of a date) are cheap: the existing calculation alre=
ady produces an as-of-today balance and could likely produce an as-of-any-d=
ate one. The trend spans are the ones that need the data-model check, worth=
 confirming with engineering before committing the trend to a near-term rel=
ease.</p>
<p><strong>Trend and comparison are wanted here</strong>, unlike on Payroll=
 Distributions. A balance drifts continuously and leadership asks which way=
 it is going, so a trend and a delta against the prior period earn their pl=
ace (Gap 4, JTBD 4 and 5). On Payroll the number is a periodic flow where p=
eriod-over-period math misleads, which is why it was rejected there. The tw=
o widgets differ because a balance and a flow differ.</p>
<h2 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-8.Gapsfoundintheliveaudit(13Jul2026)">8. Gaps foun=
d in the live audit (13 Jul 2026)</h2>
<p>Environment: asmdev, dev user, one test account, two account types. Meth=
od: DOM and accessibility-tree inspection, interaction testing, full module=
 walk. Visual layer (contrast, spacing, reflow) and high-volume behavior no=
t assessable in this pass; flagged in Section 10.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1162" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>#</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Gap</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Why it matters</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Fix direction</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Filter changes the table, not the pie; panels visibly disagree</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Consistency violation, erodes trust in the numbers</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>One filter state for both panels</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>No drill-down, and no destination exists in the module</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Below market baseline; fix requires building the destination, not wiring=
 a link</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Interim: link rows to Account Information, badges to pre-filtered report=
s labeled "Opens in Reports". Real fix: the L3 inquiry surface (Section 7)<=
/p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>No status signal (interest due, unposted interest); data lives only in r=
eports</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The module's operational heartbeat is invisible; misses surface at month=
 end</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Status badge fed by the data layer</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>4</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Balances have no comparison (delta, trend)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>"Is that good?" goes unanswered; boards engage with direction</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Delta vs prior period; trend at L3</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>5</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Pie values are hover-only; not in the DOM as text. The pie is also the o=
nly place type totals exist at all</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Fails keyboard, screen reader, touch; fails Pathway gate; the portfolio =
grain is effectively invisible</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Type summary with amounts in text (Section 7 grain decision)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>6</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The "Last refreshed" timestamp is the refresh button, and it lags filter=
 re-renders</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Freshness unreadable; a lagging stamp is worse than none for regulated f=
igures</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Separate Refresh action from a "Data as of" stamp that updates on every =
render</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>7</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>No search in the grid</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Kills the depositor-call job at real volumes</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Type-ahead by name or number</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>8</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>No Type column: the Show All list mixes accounts across types with nothi=
ng identifying each row's type. Inception Date holds a prime column instead=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The mixed list is unreadable as a portfolio; low-frequency data outranks=
 type, activity, interest status</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Add Type column; re-rank columns by job frequency (type, balance, last a=
ctivity, interest status first; inception to detail)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>9</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Widget says "Deposit Accounts", module says "Deposits On Hand", sibling =
says "Bank Balances"</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Secondary personas misread it as bank balances</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Rename the widget "Deposits On Hand" to match the module (verify "Deposi=
t Accounts" is not used in reports, statements, or training first). "Deposi=
ts on hand" can read as undeposited funds to bookkeepers, so pair the renam=
e with the info tooltip and empty state (Section 5.3)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>10</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Grid is three separate HTML tables with cells exposed as generic text; n=
o header association</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>WCAG 1.3.1 failure; screen readers hear numbers with no column context</=
p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>One semantic table, proper th scope, totals as tfoot</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>11</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Filter dropdown has no accessible or visible label (Account Information =
labels its filters correctly, so the pattern exists)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>WCAG 4.1.2 and 3.3.2; sighted users also get no hint what it filters</p>=
</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Visible "Account type" label tied to the control</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>12</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Currency and dates follow client or server culture: rendered =C2=A30.00 =
and 13/07/2026 on a US product</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Wrong currency symbol on financial figures destroys trust; root cause to=
 confirm with engineering</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Format from the organization's locale, never the client's</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>13</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Weak empty states: filtered-empty totals show "# Accounts:" with no valu=
e; no recovery offered; a 0.00 balance still draws a full pie</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Blank totals read as a bug; empty states are where P2 decides the widget=
 is broken</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Apply the widget states spec (Section 5.3)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>14</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Two accounts can have the same name and be different accounts</s=
trong>, distinguished only by account number (verified with the product own=
er). The current widget carries an Account# column that keeps them apart; a=
 redesign that drops the number to simplify the row would make same-named a=
ccounts indistinguishable</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>On regulated figures, an ambiguous row is a real error risk: staff could=
 read, cite, or act on the wrong depositor's account. Removing the account =
number is not a neutral simplification, it removes the only disambiguator</=
p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Keep every account unambiguously identifiable when names collide. Option=
s for design to weigh: show the account number (as a column, or as secondar=
y text under the name), or another stable distinguisher if one exists. Hove=
r-only disambiguation is not acceptable (accessibility constraint). The nee=
d is unambiguous identification; the mechanism is design's call</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-9.Top10insights">9. Top 10 insights</h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Design for the HQ administrator first.</strong> Headquarters mod=
ule, so P1 leads and the part-time church admin is secondary. Inverted from=
 our usual hierarchy.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>The widget's job is portfolio oversight plus fast lookup.</stron=
g> Glance-and-drill, which fits KPI-plus-grid.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>The dashboard grain is the account type, not the account.</stron=
g> A handful of types fits a glance; hundreds of depositor accounts do not.=
 Type summary at L2, account grid at L3.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Status beats data.</strong> An interest-cycle badge turns the wi=
dget into an early-warning system; today that signal exists only inside rep=
orts.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Drill-down needs a destination, and it does not exist.</strong> =
Matching the market means building the L3 inquiry surface, not adding links=
. Interim links labeled honestly ("Opens in Reports").</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Every number needs a comparison.</strong> Delta and trend, or th=
e balance answers nothing.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Trust markers are a feature.</strong> Data-as-of stamp, org-driv=
en currency and dates, interest-posted state. The live audit found failures=
 in all three.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Plain language everywhere.</strong> Volunteers and part-timers r=
un this market; no module jargon in labels.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Rights and duties in the widget.</strong> Account visibility per=
 user rights; read-and-navigate only.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Fix the chart and the grid semantics.</strong> Keep the type mix=
, lose the hover-only pie, rebuild the split tables into one semantic table=
.</p></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"DepositsOnHand-10.Openquestionsandnextsteps">10. Open questions a=
nd next steps</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Module entitlement detection (state 1): how does the platform know an or=
g has Deposits On Hand, and can the widget chooser filter on it? Engineerin=
g to confirm.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Widget rights behavior (state 2): does widget visibility respect module =
security rights today?</p></li>
<li>
<p>Rename check (Gap 9): audit where "Deposit Accounts" appears customer-fa=
cing (reports app, statements, training) before renaming.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Localization root cause (Gap 12): org setting, server culture, or browse=
r culture? US customers must always see $ and US dates.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Historical balances for the trend (7.1):</strong> can the data l=
ayer reconstruct period-end balances from the deposit transaction history (=
DHAccount), or is a balance-over-time trend a data-layer build? This gates =
the trend time-spans; the snapshot (as-of-date) spans do not depend on it.<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p>L3 scope decision: build the inquiry surface, or ship interim deep links=
 to Account Information and pre-filtered reports?</p></li>
<li>
<p>Can the reports app accept pre-filled criteria via URL, so links land on=
 a ready-to-run report instead of a blank form?</p></li>
<li>
<p>Interest status (due, unposted): is the data model ready to expose it ou=
tside reports?</p></li>
<li>
<p>Does the dashboard framework support a full-width widget, or is that fra=
mework work?</p></li>
<li>
<p>Pendo pull: what share of customers use Deposits On Hand, and how often =
is this widget selected?</p></li>
<li>
<p>Interviews: 3 to 5 headquarters customers; do they field depositor calls=
 from this screen or from reports?</p></li>
<li>
<p>Follow-up audit pass: visual layer (contrast, spacing, focus indicators,=
 reflow) and realistic data volumes (pagination, performance).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Validation: 5-user task test on an L1/L2/L3 prototype covering lookup, s=
tatus check, and drill.</p></li>
</ul>
